profile_positions.description:
Seeking interesting investment opportunities in successful Dutch (e-commerce) companies with scale-up potential.

Added-value:
As active, experienced (18 years+ in e-commerce) and dedicated investor - entrepreneur, the aim is to add value to the target company through:
* contributing entrepreneurial and e-commerce knowledge, experience and network;
* accelerating growth and professionalisation of organisation (scale-up phase);
* serving as sounding board and strategic advisor for management;
* using background and experience in corporate mergers & acquisitions for buy & build purposes.

Capable managers, e-commerce & IT-specialists can be sourced from own network, if necessary.

Investment criteria:
A suitable company ideally has the following characteristics:
* established, stable company with track record;
* recognisable specialisation in a niche segment;
* proven market position, i.e. top 3-5 player in the sector or ambition to reach that level;
* ambitious and capable entrepreneurs / management team;
* healthy gross margin potential;
* opportunities for growth acceleration and professionalisation (scale-up);
* possibility for international expansion.

The financial and organisational criteria are:
* turnover: between €3.5 - 20million;
* EBITDA: between €0.250 - 2.0million;
* employees: 5 - 50 fte;
* existing management. 

Equity interest:
Substantial minority share holding, preferably majority interest.
